🔴 Problem Statement

You are building a public API:

Users can call API to fetch data
But:
Each user can only make 5 requests per minute
If limit exceeded → block request
🧠 How to Identify Proxy Pattern?

Ask yourself:

Is there access restriction before actual logic? ✅
Is there a check happening before calling real service? ✅
Is logic like rate limit / auth / validation added? ✅

👉 This is Access Control → Proxy